Information and resources

CoV-19 is a is a novel Carona virus that was furst reported in Wuhan, China on January 20, 2020.

The virus is highly transmissable and spread:

  • Between people who are in close contact with one another (within about 6 feet).

  • Through respiratory droplets produced when an infected person coughs or sneezes.

People infeced with the virus are most contageous when they are sick, but in some cases the virus can be spread before symptoms arise

The CDC Website has more useful information

The WHO Emergency Response site also contains information on the global response to this epidemic.

ESRI has created a similar dashboard that now requires login credentials to view link

All data for this dashboard was taken from the Johns Hopkins daily CoV database hosted on [humanitarian data exchange] (https://data.humdata.org/dataset/novel-coronavirus-2019-ncov-cases)

The 2020 COV outbreak is an ongoing public health crisis and this dashboard will automatically update as more case data becomes availible

For any questions please contact: Christopher LeBoa (cleboa@stanford.edu)
